I&#39;m having a hard time seeing why this would be superior to Brian&#39;s much
simpler implementation!

I would revise Brian&#39;s method slightly though:

    static public void assertNotEquals(String message, Object shouldNotBe,
Object actual) {
        if (shouldNotBe == null) {
            assertNotNull(message, actual);
        } else if (shouldNotBe.equals(actual)) {
            failEquals(message, shouldNotBe);
        }
    }
    static public void assertNotEquals(Object shouldNotBe, Object actual) {
        assertNotEquals(null, shouldNotBe, actual);
    }
    static private void failEquals(String message, Object shouldNotBe) {
        String formatted= &quot;&quot;;
        if (message != null)
            formatted= message+&quot; &quot;;
        fail(formatted+&quot;expected not to be:&lt;&quot;+shouldNotBe+&quot;&gt;&quot;);
    }

Kevin


